    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Supporters of the 2024 tax reform bill argue that reducing corporate tax rates will stimulate economic growth by encouraging businesses to invest more, create jobs, and expand operations. They believe that these benefits will trickle down to the broader economy, ultimately benefiting everyone, including the middle and lower classes. Additionally, proponents claim that the tax cuts will lead to increased consumer spending and higher wages, which will help reduce wealth inequality. They also argue that the bill will attract foreign investment, boost the competitiveness of American businesses, and lead to a stronger, more resilient economy. However, critics contend that these potential benefits are overstated and that the tax cuts primarily benefit the wealthy and large corporations, exacerbating wealth inequality in the long run.",
